President Cyril Ramaphosa has asked that Jacob Zuma be given time and space to think things through. #DStv403​ #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has asked that Jacob Zuma be given time and space to think things through. Ramaphosa was speaking outside the home of the late ANC stalwart, Rebecca Kotane, on Friday. The former president is refusing to appear before the Zondo Commission. READ: Zuma hosts Malema for tea at Nkandla Zuma still contends that Justice Raymond Zondo is conflicted and biased, and should recuse himself. "He has expressed his own thoughts and views that he does not want to go to the commission," Ramaphosa says. Meanwhile, Zuma hosted EFF leader Julius Malema, at his home in Nkandla on Friday. Watch the video above for more details on this story.